---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "QQQI Dividend Analysis & History",
    "description": "Analyze the ultra-high yield of QQQI, its options-based income strategy, and track its historical monthly distributions.",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Westmount Fundamentals"
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Where can I find the qqqi dividend history?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "You can review the complete qqqi dividend history on our platform, detailing the varying monthly payouts generated by its covered call options strategy."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How does the qqqi dividend work?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The qqqi dividend is generated by holding Nasdaq-100 stocks and selling out-of-the-money call options. The premiums collected from these options are distributed to shareholders monthly."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the current qqqi dividend yield?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The 12-month trailing qqqi dividend yield is exceptionally high, currently sitting around 14.22%. It fluctuates significantly based on Nasdaq volatility."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "When is the next qqqi dividend date?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "QQQI distributes income monthly. The typical qqqi dividend date falls near the 20th to 25th of every month."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do I use a qqqi dividend calculator?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Enter your share count and average purchase price into our qqqi dividend calculator to instantly project your massive monthly and annual passive income stream."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the expected qqqi dividend yield 2025?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Assuming tech volatility remains elevated, the qqqi dividend yield 2025 is projected to remain well into the double digits, continuing its trend of massive income generation."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];
---

<SiteLayout
  site="westmount"
  title="QQQI Dividend Analysis & History"
  description="Is a 14%+ yield too good to be true? We break down QQQI's payout strategy, its monthly history, and project your cash flow."
  canonical="https://westmountfundamentals.com/qqqi-dividend-history"
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>QQQI Dividend Analysis & History</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Monthly options income, tech sector yield, and advanced cash flow calculator</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>QQQI Dividend Profile</h2>
      <p>The NEOS Nasdaq-100 High Income ETF (QQQI) offers a unique approach to generating massive income from the technology sector. By employing a data-driven call option strategy on the Nasdaq-100, it aims to deliver double-digit yields while still capturing a portion of the underlying index's upside.</p>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Current Yield & Metrics</h3>
        <table>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <th>Current Trailing Yield</th>
              <td>14.22%</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Payout Frequency</th>
              <td>Monthly</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Price-to-Earnings (P/E)</th>
              <td>32.67</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Expense Ratio</th>
              <td>0.68%</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p>Because QQQI relies on option premiums for its massive yield, payouts will fluctuate based on the implied volatility of the Nasdaq-100. For investors seeking massive current income rather than pure capital growth, it represents a compelling alternative. Compare this tech-focused approach to the more defensive <a href="/jepi-dividend">JEPI Dividend strategy</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Monthly Dividend History</h2>
      <p>QQQI distributes its option premiums monthly. The table below outlines the historical payouts generated by this high-income strategy.</p>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Ex-Dividend Date</th>
            <th>Amount ($)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>2026-02-18</td><td>$0.6140</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2026-01-21</td><td>$0.6360</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-12-24</td><td>$0.6410</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-11-26</td><td>$0.6300</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-10-22</td><td>$0.6450</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-09-24</td><td>$0.6410</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-08-20</td><td>$0.6290</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-07-23</td><td>$0.6370</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-06-25</td><td>$0.6280</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-05-21</td><td>$0.6370</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-04-23</td><td>$0.5310</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-03-26</td><td>$0.5870</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-02-26</td><td>$0.6140</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-01-22</td><td>$0.6240</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2024-12-24</td><td>$0.6220</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2024-11-20</td><td>$0.6120</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2024-10-23</td><td>$0.6100</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2024-09-25</td><td>$0.6020</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2024-08-21</td><td>$0.6440</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2024-07-24</td><td>$0.6190</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2024-06-26</td><td>$0.6230</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2024-05-22</td><td>$0.6130</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2024-04-24</td><td>$0.5870</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2024-03-20</td><td>$0.6050</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2024-02-21</td><td>$0.5940</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>High-Yield Reinvestment Calculator</h2>
      <p>With yields frequently exceeding 14%, compounding happens rapidly. Input your share count to estimate your monthly cash flow.</p>

      <div class="card" id="calc-container">
        <label style="display:block; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:0.5rem; color:var(--text-secondary);">Number of Shares Owned</label>
        <input type="number" id="sharesInput" placeholder="e.g. 200" style="width:100%; padding:0.75rem; border-radius:8px; border:1px solid var(--border-color); background:var(--bg-color); color:var(--text-primary); font-size:1rem; margin-bottom:1rem;" />

        <label style="display:block; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:0.5rem; color:var(--text-secondary);">Average Price per Share ($)</label>
        <input type="number" id="priceInput" placeholder="e.g. 50.00" style="width:100%; padding:0.75rem; border-radius:8px; border:1px solid var(--border-color); background:var(--bg-color); color:var(--text-primary); font-size:1rem; margin-bottom:1.5rem;" />

        <button id="calculateBtn" style="background:var(--accent-color); color:#fff; padding:0.75rem 1.5rem; border:none; border-radius:8px; font-weight:600; cursor:pointer; width:100%; font-size:1rem;">Calculate Income</button>

        <div id="results" style="display:none; margin-top:1.5rem; padding-top:1.5rem; border-top:1px solid var(--border-color);">
          <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">
            <span style="color:var(--text-secondary);">Estimated Annual Income:</span>
            <span id="annualIncome" style="font-weight:700; color:var(--accent-color);">$0.00</span>
          </div>
          <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between;">
            <span style="color:var(--text-secondary);">Estimated Monthly Payout:</span>
            <span id="monthlyIncome" style="font-weight:700;">$0.00</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details>
        <summary>Where can I find the qqqi dividend history?</summary>
        <p>You can review the complete qqqi dividend history on our platform, detailing the varying monthly payouts generated by its covered call options strategy.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How does the qqqi dividend work?</summary>
        <p>The qqqi dividend is generated by holding Nasdaq-100 stocks and selling out-of-the-money call options. The premiums collected from these options are distributed to shareholders monthly.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the current qqqi dividend yield?</summary>
        <p>The 12-month trailing qqqi dividend yield is exceptionally high, currently sitting around 14.22%. It fluctuates significantly based on Nasdaq volatility.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>When is the next qqqi dividend date?</summary>
        <p>QQQI distributes income monthly. The typical qqqi dividend date falls near the 20th to 25th of every month.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How do I use a qqqi dividend calculator?</summary>
        <p>Enter your share count and average purchase price into our qqqi dividend calculator to instantly project your massive monthly and annual passive income stream.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the expected qqqi dividend yield 2025?</summary>
        <p>Assuming tech volatility remains elevated, the qqqi dividend yield 2025 is projected to remain well into the double digits, continuing its trend of massive income generation.</p>
      </details>
    </section>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
      const btn = document.getElementById('calculateBtn');
      const sharesInput = document.getElementById('sharesInput');
      const priceInput = document.getElementById('priceInput');
      const resultsDiv = document.getElementById('results');
      const annualSpan = document.getElementById('annualIncome');
      const monthlySpan = document.getElementById('monthlyIncome');

      const YIELD = 0.1422; // 14.22%

      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const shares = parseFloat(sharesInput.value) || 0;
        const price = parseFloat(priceInput.value) || 0;

        const totalValue = shares * price;
        const annual = totalValue * YIELD;
        const monthly = annual / 12;

        annualSpan.textContent = '$' + annual.toLocaleString(undefined, {minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2});
        monthlySpan.textContent = '$' + monthly.toLocaleString(undefined, {minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2});

        resultsDiv.style.display = 'block';
      });
    });
  </script>

  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .subtitle { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; }
    .card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    th, td { padding: 0.75rem 1rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    th { font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .faq-section details { margin: 1rem 0; padding: 1rem; background: var(--card-bg); border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    .faq-section summary { font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; }
    a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
    a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
